    - target: {fileID: 2636065031202590820, guid: ed7b740a5cf36044ab197a19d1fe05ab, type: 3}
      propertyPath: m_text
      value: "The Minoans were a Bronze Age civilization centered on Crete (c. 2000\u20131400
        BCE), known for their palace complexes, vivid frescoes, and far-reaching
        Aegean trade. Among their art, the crocus held notable cultural relevance.\r\n"
